# Cloudflare Pages redirects
#
# API and /health are handled by the frontend code itself: when
# VITE_BACKEND_URL is set (in .env.production), api.js / eduApi.js prepend
# the Railway URL to every /api request. So we don't need the Pages-level
# proxy any more — the previous /api/* and /health 200-rewrites were being
# rejected anyway because Cloudflare Pages doesn't allow proxy rewrites
# to remote hosts.
#
# SPA fallback: serve index.html for any path that isn't a real file
# (covers deep links like /districts?district=qoqon_city when accessed
# directly). Pattern below excludes paths that contain a dot (which are
# treated as static assets) so it doesn't cause an infinite-loop warning.
/:path([^.]*)        /index.html        200
